### Test Authentication Endpoints

### 1. Check registration mode (public)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/registration-mode

### 2. Register new user (when public mode)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "password_confirmation": "password123"
}

### 3. Login
POST http://localhost:8000/api/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "password"
}

### 4. Get current user (requires token from login)
GET http://localhost:8000/api/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Admin: Get all users
GET http://localhost:8000/api/admin/users
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Admin: Create user manually
POST http://localhost:8000/api/admin/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Admin Created User",
  "email": "admincreated@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "user"
}

### 7. Admin: Update registration mode to admin_only
PUT http://localhost:8000/api/admin/settings/registration-mode
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "mode": "admin_only"
}

### 8. Try to register when admin_only (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8000/api/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Should Fail",
  "email": "fail@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "password_confirmation": "password123"
}

### 9. Logout
POST http://localhost:8000/api/logout
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE
